summary: Woke late at 9am after fragmented sleep. Felt higher energy than usual despite incomplete rest. Attended a therapy session and technical interview at Coffe.io, handled interview with ~90% confidence. Felt anxious but managed it better than before. Experienced an energetic, hypomanic-like period in the evening but successfully nudged myself back to routine. Ended the day calmer and more regulated.

wins: Handled anxiety better than usual during interview.
Maintained self-regulation during evening hypomanic-like energy surge.
Successfully returned to routine after high-energy period.
losses: Sleep was fragmented and less restorative.
Felt overwhelmed after a hectic day.
ideas: Track energetic surges and hypomanic-like periods to see patterns.
Consider small wind-down strategies after high-stimulation events.

goals: Continue practicing gentle routine adherence even during high-energy or anxious states.
Monitor sleep fragmentation and aim for better night consistency.
triggerEvents: Evening walk with music and CBT discussion
